==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[aconitum]]'', Greek: compare French [[aconit]]

===Noun===
'''aconite'''

#''(Botany):'' The herb [[wolfsbane]], or [[monkshood]]; -- applied to any plant of the genus ''[[Aconitum]]'' (tribe [[Hellebore]]), all the species of which are poisonous.
#An extract or tincture obtained from ''Aconitum [[napellus]]'', used as a poison and medicinally. 

===Derived terms===
*'''Winter aconite:''' a plant ''[[Eranthis]] [[hyemalis]]'' allied to the aconites.

